<br>
&quot;Maybe this was a bad idea.  I could very well be mistaken.  But then again what if what the others said is true...I must ask&quot;<br>
<br>
Drizle straightens up and enters the guildhall just as a warrior of the Vah Shir should, proudly.  Several people stop their talking to look at her.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh dear,&quot; she thinks,&quot;I hope they like Vha Shir, I dont think I could take on this many poeple.&quot;<br>
<br>
   She then notices a high elf woman coming towards her, followed by another.  They carry themselves with confidence and seem to exude a power all their own. <br>
   The mark on Drizle's palm sends a sensation through her arm.  She starts a bit, until today the only thing she had felt from that blasted mark was pain.  Now it is warm and almost soothing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hello,&quot; says one of the High elf women,&quot; I am Solarianne, this,&quot; she gestures to the robed woman next to her,&quot;is Ennya.  Do not fear, you are among friends.  What has lead you to our guildhall this eve?&quot; she gestures to a nearby table, Drizle follows their lead and sits, wrapping her tail around to rest on her lap.<br>
<br>
Drizle eyes Solarianne and Ennya warily, but the warm pulse in her hands only gets stronger, as if the mark itself was trying to reassure her.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have come seeking answers to a puzzle.  The name of your guild caused my brain to turn and think about something other than killing.  When I was born,  i had a strange mark on my palm.  The elders called it a blessing,  while their apprentices felt certain it was a curse.  <br>
   When I was still quite young, a pain began to grow in my hand.  It spread through my arm and caused me never ending misery.   <br>
          One day, while I was wandering outside of Shar Vahl, i came upon a rusty sword.  It was nothing special, but i felt compelled to pick it up, after all, someone could get hurt if they stepped on it.  The mark on my hand burned even greater when i touched it.  I started to quiver with anticipation,  all my hair was stood on end, and i felt sudden and immediate danger.  <br>
         Just then a juvenile rockhopper jumped on my back.  Normally they are kept away from the borders city , but this one had slipped in unnoticed.  <br>
         I managed to shake him off and gave him a good swat with my free paw.  He tumbled head over heels and before he could regain his footing I brought the old sword straight down upon his head.  He let out a screech and then fell silent.  Then, I noticed something..the pain in my arm had gone.  I dropped the sword and looked at the mark of my birth.  I could clearly see now that it was a tear.  It pulsed with a warm glow, and slowly, pulse by pulse the glow faded, and the pain returned.<br>
    Please tell me,&quot; Drizle said her eyes beginning to glaze over with unwarriorlike tears,&quot;do you know what this mark could mean, and if you do, how can i be rid of it.&quot;   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umoline.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moline</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/02 9:15:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=95.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hello, I am Drizle</span><hr size=1> Moline packs away her lute for the night..  tired and weary from the song requests that have been coming in steady all evening...  She orders an elven wine and looks around for somewhere to sit down and relax..  just then she notices a furry critter sitting near Ennya and Solarianne...  she wonders why there are tears in her eyes..  Moline gets her elven wine and goes to sit down at the table with the three who look deep into conversation<br>
<br>
&quot;I hope it's okay I sit down and talk with you all.  You look so upset I couldn't help but notice.&quot;<br>
<br>
Moline sits down and listens to the story Drizle has to tell.<br>
<br>
&quot;well dear kitty it seems you have come to the right place.&quot;<br>
<br>
Moline notices the tears in Drizle's eyes clear up some.  <br>
<br>
&quot;you see Drizle we are all marked with a similar mark. &quot;  Moline shows Drizle the mark she has on her ankle.  It's somewhat faded but very distinct in it's tear shape.  &quot;I was born with mine.  It becomes very bright when dragons are near!&quot;<br>
<br>
Drizle looks at Moline's birthmark with astonishment.  &quot;so what does this all mean?&quot;, Drizzle says.<br>
<br>
&quot;tell us more of your adventures Drizle&quot;, says Ennya.<br>
<br>
&quot;yes.  tell us more dear.  how many seasons have you?.  who do we have to thank for sending you to our guildhall?&quot;<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utalcee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talcee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tears of Veeshan</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/6/02 6:46:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=95.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hello, I am Drizle</span><hr size=1> Talcee, with her comfortable chair close to the fire, sleeps.  She slips into a dream...a dream of hunting in Faydwer again with her brother, Dankin, as they slayed the Drake dragonspawn in Steamfont.  But that was long ago....The shaman awakens with a start, as the Tear-shaped mark on her neck burns.  <br>
<br>
Talcee looks around and sees that it is late, but that Moline, Solarianne, and Ennya are speaking with a vah shir.  As she approaches, she hears ennya say, &quot;Tell us more of your adventures Drizle.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes. Tell us more dear. How many seasons have you? Who do we have to thank for sending you to our guildhall?&quot;<br>
<br>
The Barbarian smiles in welcome.  &quot;Hail, lassie.  I hope that I dunna interrupt ye.  I see ye have tha Mark on ye, and that ye have found us.&quot;<br>
