<br>
&quot;Well,&quot; she begins clumsily,&quot;As I told you before, the mark on my palm gives me great pain except when I am in battle.  With a weapon in hand and an enemy in front of me, the pain subsides.  After my first kill, I decided to become a warrior for the Vah Shir.  My parents were hoping I would take the path of a Shaman or Beastlord, but were still happy I did not chose the rogue path.  I began my training and have been slaying Loda Kai bandits in my lands, as well as trying to clear out Paludral caverns of the Phlarg fiends that interrupt the smooth trading from Shadow Haven to Shar Vahl.  <br>
<br>
I have reached my 18th season as of this moment.<br>
<br>
All I can think of is when the next battle will be, and how I can stop this pain.  If this mark I have is what you say it is, it would seem then that I must vanquish this land of dragons and all who would aide them.  I have never seen one, and to tell the truth heard very very little about them.  I know they are beings of great power, but if relief from this never ending pain lies within their knowledge, or blood, then it is them I shall seek.<br>
<br>
But I must tell you something now.  When you Solarianne and you Ennya,&quot;Drizle looks at both in turn,&quot; approached me this evening the pain began to withdraw, and a different feeling has come from the mark.&quot; she looks at the others who have gathered to hear her story,&quot;I feel no pain here.&quot;   She tries to look calm and collected, but truly she is just as fascinated with them.  She has never been so close to other races.  She has seen many travelers, but this is her first close experience with sentient poeples who are not Vah Shir, or Loda Kai.<br>
<br>
She studies the faces of those around her, and with each new set of eyes her mark warms and pulses reassuringly.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Could this be my place in the universe?&quot; she thinks,&quot; I hope they will accept me as a friend.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umirahze521.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mirahze521</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tears of Veeshan</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/7/02 3:52:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=95.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hello, I am Drizle</span><hr size=1> Salvia sits under the table where Solarianne and Ennya are listening to the tale of a newcomer.  She begins to wonder why they chose the table she was snoozing under to sit at, but the story she hears fascinates her.  The mark on her shoulder begins to warm with each word Drizle utters.  <br>
<br>
When the tale is over she slides out from under the table and sits in front of Drizle.  The large vah shir starts at the appearance of a wolf at her feet, but Salvia nuzzles her knee and the warrior calms a bit.  <br>
<br>
Then with a look at her guildmates and another long look at this new face, Salvia throws her head back in a wild howl of acceptance and joy, she then turns to Ennya for a snack.<br>
<br>
